newsArray.title: Bechem United coach Desmond-Issah Botchway confident ahead of Aduana Stars clash
newsArray.description: Bechem United coach Desmond-Issah Botchway remains optimistic as his side prepares for a tough test against Aduana Stars on Sunday, October 12.The Hunters are yet to record a win this season but the coach believes his team is ready to turn things around."Aduana Stars is a big team. Any time you are going to play against them we have to prepare well. They play very good football so we have to prepare well. So we are coming up with a very good team," Botchway told Bechem United TV.Bechem United currently sits 15th on the Ghana Premier League table with two points after four games, having drawn two and lost two. Aduana Stars, on the other hand, occupy 9th place with six points and will be looking to continue their steady form at home.Despite the difference in standings, Botchwayâs side is determined to put up a strong fight in Dormaa as they search for their first victory of the 2025/26 campaign.
